    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5027484>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Astiotrema reniferum (Looss, 1898) Looss, 1900 revealing some intra-specific variations in esophagus extension, vitellarium distribution and maturation, testes configuration, and ovary shape. 1. A. reniferum (Syn. Distomum unicum Looss, 1896 nec Molin, 1859), ventral view, redrawn from Looss (1896, fig. 20). 2. A. reniferum (Syn. Astiotrema giganticum Tiwari, 1958), dorsal view, redrawn from Tiwari (1958, fig. 1). 3. A. reniferum (Syn. Astiotrema thapari Gupta, 1954), ventral view, redrawn from Gupta (1954, fig. 4). 4. A. reniferum (Syn. Astiotrema loossii Mehra, 1931), dorsal view, redrawn from Mehra (1931b, p. 187). 5. A. reniferum (Syn. A. loossii), ventral view, redrawn from Dwivedi (1966, fig. 2). Abbreviations: AT, anterior testis; Ce, cecum; CP, cirrus-pouch; Eg, eggs; EP, excretory pore; Es, esophagus; EV, excretory vesicle; GP, genital pore; LC, Laurel’s canal; Oo, oötype; OS, oral sucker; Ov, ovary; Ph, pharynx; PP, pars prostatica; PT, posterior testis; SR, seminal receptacle; SV, seminal vesicle; Ut, uterus; VD, vitelline duct; V-D, vas-deferens; VF, vitelline follicle; VS, ventral sucker. Scale bars: Fig. 1 = 1,000 µm; Fig. 2 = 2,000 µm; Fig. 3 =2,000 µm; Fig. 4 = 500 µm; Fig. 5 = 1,000 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5027484/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

